====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive|order and arrangement}} To [[arrange]] or [[order]] in a row.

===Etymology 4===
{{etymid|en|bench}}
Probably from {{der|en|fr|banc}}. Of {{der|en|gem}} origin, and akin to English {{m|en|bench}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[bench]], as for rowers in a galley; also, a tier of oars.
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1658|author=w:Edmund Waller|title=he Passion of Dido for Ã†neas
|passage=Placed on their '''banks''', the lusty Trojans sweep / Neptune's smooth face, and cleave the yielding deep.}}
# A bench or seat for [[judge]]s in [[court]].
# The regular [[term]] of a court of law, or the full court sitting to hear arguments upon questions of law, as distinguished from a sitting at [[nisi prius]], or a court held for jury trials. See {{m|en|banc}}<ref>{{R:Burrill Law Dictionary}}</ref>
# {{lb|en|archaic|printing}} A kind of [[table]] used by [[printer]]s.
# {{lb|en|music}} A bench, or row of keys belonging to a [[keyboard]], as in an [[organ]].<ref>{{R:Knight AMD}}</ref>

